Japanese car maker curb export European Community ( EC ) following unofficial directive Ministry International Trade Industry ( MITI ) , automobile industry source said .
Some source said export EC year likely unchanged last year 's 1.10 mln unit may even fall due anticipated slackening EC economic growth increasing trade friction .
Last week , MITI vice minister international affair Makoto Kuroda said ministry asked car maker exercise prudence exporting Europe .
